The article announces that the United States has met its goal of admitting 10,000 Syrian refugees this fiscal year, ahead of schedule. This decision was made in response to the global refugee crisis and the President's desire to send a message of support to the Syrian people and the international community. The article also mentions that the United States will admit at least 85,000 refugees in total this year from various countries. The achievement is attributed to the hard work of government employees and the support of international organizations and NGOs. The article concludes by highlighting the ongoing efforts to address the global humanitarian crisis and the upcoming Leaders' Summit on Refugees.